                            <comment id="16184060" author="githubbot" created="Thu, 28 Sep 2017 12:14:00 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;GitHub user dguy opened a pull request:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;    &lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/apache/kafka/pull/3983&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://github.com/apache/kafka/pull/3983&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;    &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/KAFKA-5986&quot; title=&quot;Streams State Restoration never completes when logging is disabled&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;KAFKA-5986&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;KAFKA-5986&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;: Streams State Restoration never completes when logging is disabled&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;    When logging is disabled and there are state stores the task never transitions from restoring to running. This is because we only ever check if the task has state stores and return false on initialization if it does. The check should be if we have changelog partitions, i.e., we need to restore.&lt;/p&gt;

